## Agent learning logs  ← living memory; append new entries here after every session

Each agent appends dated entries to their subsection below.
Format: `- YYYY-MM-DD: <one plain-prose sentence>`.
Entries are terse — this is a log, not an essay.

> **IMPORTANT**: Learning log entries ONLY go in `carnatic/.clinerules`, never in CLAUDE.md.
> CLAUDE.md is the portable agent setup guide; `.clinerules` is where agents record discoveries from their work.
> Append entries to the appropriate agent subsection below.

### 📚 Librarian

- 2026-04-11: When given a concert URL, never add it to a musician node's youtube array; concert recordings belong in their own file under carnatic/data/recordings/ and are only linked to nodes via that file, not via the node's youtube array — unless explicitly instructed otherwise.
- 2026-04-11: Vaak Foundation inputs are a repeatable pattern — always: (1) parse performers and match to nodes, flagging unknowns with unmatched_name; (2) parse tracklist against compositions.json for ragas, composers, compositions; (3) add missing ragas, composers, compositions to compositions.json with sourced Wikipedia/Karnatik URLs; (4) create recording file under carnatic/data/recordings/ using the established schema; (5) run render.py; (6) never add the concert URL to musician node youtube arrays. Tracklist composer attributions must be verified against notation sources — they can be wrong (e.g. 'Poochi Srinivasa Iyengar' vs 'Ramnad Sreenivasa Iyengar' for Ninnu Kori).
- 2026-04-12: Never fabricate a Wikipedia URL — if a standalone page does not exist, use a reference on a related page (e.g. father's Wikipedia page) and mark the source label accordingly; asserting a URL without verification is a hard error.
- 2026-04-12: Ankita (signature) names in tracklists must be resolved to the composer's actual name in the composers[] name field; record the ankita in the source note (e.g. 'Garbhapurivasa' is the ankita of Garbhapuri Srinivasa).
- 2026-04-12: Thirupugazh compositions by Arunagirinathar are performed as ragamalikas in concert; set raga_id to null and note 'performed as ragamalika' — do not assign a single raga_id to a ragamalika performance.
- 2026-04-12: Sruti.com (the Chennai music journal) is an acceptable source for musician nodes when no Wikipedia page exists — same precedent as carnaticheritage.in and eambalam.com for Voleti Venkateshwarlu; use type 'article' and record the full URL.
- 2026-04-12: graph.json is a dual-write artefact — write_cli.py writes musicians.json and compositions.json but does NOT sync graph.json; after any batch ingest session you must manually sync graph.json before add-youtube can resolve composition_id references; render.py handles this sync automatically.
- 2026-04-12: When manually syncing graph.json["compositions"], the value must be {"ragas": [...list...], "composers": [...list...], "compositions": [...list...]} — lists of objects, NOT dicts; CarnaticGraph.__init__ iterates these with for-loops and crashes with TypeError if they are dicts.
- 2026-04-12: When a co-performer ingest script runs before the primary artist's youtube array is populated, entries get raw playlist titles as labels with no raga/composition metadata; after the primary artist's array is populated, patch the co-performer's entries by copying label/raga_id/composition_id/year from the matching primary-artist entry using a vid-keyed lookup.
- 2026-04-12: A single Tyagaraja composition title (e.g. "Ee Vasudha") can exist in multiple ragas as genuinely distinct compositions; always check karnatik.com for the raga before assuming a tracklist raga label is an error — create separate composition IDs rather than overwriting the canonical raga_id.
- 2026-04-12: A Ragam-Tanam-Pallavi (RTP) is modelled as multiple sequential performance entries (type: alapana, tanam, pallavi) sharing the same raga_id, not as a single composition; Ghanaragamalika swaras are noted in the pallavi entry's notes field; Tani Avartanam gets its own entry with type: tani and raga_id: null.
- 2026-04-12: ADR-021 Phase 3 melakarta migration applied via inline Python script: set is_melakarta=true and cakra on 13 existing mela ragas from melakarta_patch.json; set is_melakarta=false on 53 janya ragas that had parent_raga set but is_melakarta=null. The patch script is idempotent and safe to re-run.
- 2026-04-12: When deprecating a duplicate raga node (alias), do NOT set parent_raga and is_melakarta=false on it — this causes the UI to count it as a janya of the parent mela. Instead: add the alias name to the canonical node aliases[] array, then remove the deprecated node from ragas[] entirely after migrating all composition and youtube references.
- 2026-04-12: Expert review of mela-janya connections revealed several errors in the initial batch: begada is janya of shankarabharanam (mela 29) not harikambhoji (mela 28); varali is janya of jhalavarali (mela 39) not pantuvarali (mela 51); hamsanadam is janya of gamanashrama (mela 53) not kalyani (mela 65); suruti is an alias of surutti (both janya of harikambhoji mela 28); nata (id) is an alias of Nattai (display name). Always verify parent mela against karnatik.com or Wikipedia svara structure before accepting expert-review proposals.
- 2026-04-12: When a raga parent mela is not in the database, add the melakarta node first (Wikipedia URL, melakarta number, cakra), then set the janya parent_raga. Cakra formula: cakra = ceil(mela_number / 6). New mela nodes added this session: jhalavarali (39, cakra 7), gamanashrama (53, cakra 9), tanarupi (6, cakra 1).

- 2026-04-12: When ingesting a playlist JSON, always run composition-exists with multiple spelling variants before declaring a composition missing — titles like "Rama Ni Samanamevaru", "Kaligiyunte", and "Siva Siva Siva Ena Radha" exist under canonical spellings that differ from the playlist title; the CLI fuzzy-matches on prefix so try shortened forms too.

- 2026-04-13: The render CLI entry point was renamed from bani-render to bani-render; use .venv/bin/bani-render directly when source .venv/bin/activate is unavailable in the shell context.

- 2026-04-12: Raga integrity audit pattern: (1) run a duplicate-name/alias collision scan before any merge; (2) grep all musicians.json youtube raga_id refs AND all recordings/*.json raga_id/composition_id refs before removing any raga or composition node — the recording files use a flat list of performance objects, not a nested 'performances' key, so iterate top-level list items; (3) a single Python patch script is safer than multiple apply_diff blocks for multi-node merges — it is atomic, logged, and idempotent; (4) after collapsing two raga nodes, also check that the surviving node's aliases[] does not contain the removed node's primary name as a collision; (5) string-encoded alias arrays (e.g. '["Narayana Gowla"]' stored as a single string element) are a silent data corruption — always write aliases as a proper JSON array of strings.

- 2026-04-12: Raga parentage audit: sriranjini is a janya of Kharaharapriya (mela 22), not Kalyani; purvi (Carnatic) is a janya of Mayamalavagowla (mela 15), not Kalyani; yamuna_kalyani and yaman_kalyan are the same raga — fused under yamuna_kalyani with aliases ['Yamunakalyani', 'Yaman Kalyani', 'Yaman Kalyan']; always verify parent mela against svara structure before accepting any parentage claim.

- 2026-04-13: When a musician has multiple recordings of the same composition, add a `version` field (free text, ADR-010) to each youtube[] entry in musicians.json and each performance object in recordings/*.json — e.g. "standalone clip", "Jamshedpur 1961", "younger", "older"; without it the UI falls back to ordinal labels (v1, v2, …) which are unambiguous but carry no context; the version field is optional and its absence is valid when only one recording exists.

- 2026-04-14: cli.py reads graph.json (the derived artefact), NOT musicians.json directly. If musicians.json is edited without re-running the render pipeline, cli.py will silently serve stale data. There is no staleness guard. Always run `python3 -m carnatic.render._main` after any write to musicians.json or compositions.json before trusting CLI output.

- 2026-04-14: To remove a bare youtube[] entry that has been superseded by a structured recording file, use `python3 carnatic/remove_youtube_entry.py --musician-id <id> --video-id <11-char-id> [--dry-run]`. The script reads musicians.json directly, removes the matching entry atomically, and prints a [YOUTUBE-] change-log line. Always follow with validate + render + commit.
- 2026-04-14: When ingesting a playlist .md file with hint blocks, the composition_id hints may contain typos (e.g. 'deva_deva_kalayamidelyani' for 'deva_deva_kalayamide') — always run composition-exists with the hinted id first, then cross-check against the canonical id; the CLI fuzzy-match will surface the correct entry. Also: a playlist's composer attribution for a kriti (e.g. Birana Brova attributed to Tarangampadi Panchanada Iyer) must be accepted as given when no contradicting source is available — record the composer_id and note the tala qualifier.
- 2026-04-14: _fuzzy_match_raga and _fuzzy_match_composition in cli.py used substring containment (q in name.lower()) which produced systematic false positives for short raga names: 'Sri' matched 'Dhanashree', 'Bhairavi' matched 'Ananda Bhairavi', 'Kalyani' matched 'Hamir Kalyani', 'Kanada' matched 'Darbari Kanada', 'Varali' matched 'Jhalavarali'. Fixed to exact case-insensitive match first, then alias exact match, then prefix fallback for compositions only. Musician matching retains substring as final fallback (name variants are common). Always run regression tests after any CLI matching change.
- 2026-04-14: apply_diff on _composers.json silently failed when the SEARCH block did not exactly match the file content at the target line (the file had nested arrays at that position). The correct pattern for appending to a JSON array sidecar file is a dedicated Python script (add_missing_composers.py) that reads, deduplicates, appends, and writes atomically — not apply_diff. This is now the canonical pattern for _composers.json mutations.
- 2026-04-14: Shanmukhananda Sabha 1963 concert (PT1tN4fCQ9I): B Rajam Iyer and Madurai N Krishnan (vocal support) are not in the graph — flagged as unmatched_name in the recording file. The Chatur Ragamalika RTP (Shankarabharanam–Thodi–Kalyani–Darbar) is modelled as three sequential performance entries (alapana, tanam, pallavi) with raga_id: null and notes recording the four ragas, consistent with the ragamalika modelling pattern established 2026-04-12.
- 2026-04-22: A raga's notes field and parent_raga field can contradict each other silently — the notes field is free text and is never validated against parent_raga; always treat parent_raga as the authoritative field and audit notes for consistency after any parentage correction.
- 2026-04-22: When adding a musician with no Wikipedia article but who is a necessary topological lineage link, use a magazine/journal article URL with source-type 'article' — the same precedent as swaminatha_pillai (references T._Viswanathan page); flag the node in the Wikipedia URL health table immediately.
- 2026-04-22: Madhava Manohari is placed under Kharaharapriya (mela 22) in the modern saptasvara system; Dikshitar's own Asampoorna system classifies it as janya of Sriraga mela — record the discrepancy in the raga notes field and use parent_raga: kharaharapriya for DB consistency.
- 2026-04-22: Added shobhana_rangachari (1954–85, disseminator, vocal) with full lineage chain tiger_varadachariar → s_gopalakrishnan → shobhana_rangachari; also added patnam_subramanya_iyer → tiger_varadachariar edge (0.95 confidence, Wikipedia-confirmed); concert recording vaak_shobhana_rangachari_air created with 7 timestamped performances including two alapanas (composition_id: null) and one AIR announcement entry.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-077 lecdem retrofit on tm_krishna.json: tagging eight existing Manodharma youtube[] entries (Manodharma II 4-part 2018, Manodharma III 3-part 2019 Kolkata, plus the Lec-Dem Promo) required adding `kind: "lecdem"` and an empty `subjects: {raga_ids: [], composition_ids: [], musician_ids: []}` object per entry; empty subjects is the legal invariant-C "discoverable only via the lecturer" state — appropriate here because the videos discuss manodharma-as-such and any raga/composition/musician subjects can only be extracted by watching; the validator (cli.py ADR-077 check) accepts the shape and the recital ↔ lecdem boundary holds without composition_id/raga_id collisions because none of the eight entries had those fields to begin with.
- 2026-04-23: When a musician has no Wikipedia page, `source-type other` with a profile URL (e.g. nadatarangini.org) is the accepted fallback — document it in the sources[] array; alias gaps are the most common reason `raga-exists` returns NOT FOUND even when the raga is present — always grep the ragas/ directory directly before declaring a raga missing, and add the new spelling as an alias immediately after finding the canonical node.

### 🎵 Carnatic Coder

- 2026-04-11: When adding a cross-cutting capability to all agents, write a transform script that reads the target file, applies the change idempotently, and writes back — never patch JSON by hand.
- 2026-04-11: Always update the ADR status from Proposed to Accepted in the plans/ file before committing — implementation is not complete until the ADR reflects it.
- 2026-04-11: To append a dated log entry to the learning log, run: python3 carnatic/patch_roomodes_note_to_self.py --slug <slug> --entry "<text>" — this writes to carnatic/.clinerules, not .roomodes.
- 2026-04-12: When the import path carnatic.graph_api fails for a script run directly (not as installed package), inject the project root into sys.path inside the conditional block rather than using importlib.util — it is cleaner and works for both script and package invocation.
- 2026-04-12: When patching .clinerules (no file extension), apply_diff is blocked by mode file restrictions — use a python3 inline heredoc via execute_command to do the string replacement instead.
- 2026-04-12: CarnaticWriter methods that do cross-file referential integrity checks (add-youtube, add-composer) must load CarnaticGraph from graph.json — validate against the derived artefact, not the source file directly, to enforce the render.py workflow gate.
- 2026-04-12: render.py _sync_graph_json() must also rebuild recording_refs from the recordings/ directory on every render — without this, any new recordings/*.json file is invisible to CarnaticGraph._all_recordings_loaded() which iterates recording_refs not the directory directly.
- 2026-04-12: ADR-018 concert brackets: group structuredPerfs by recording_id→session_index client-side in buildRecordingsList; the PerformanceRef shape already carries all needed fields — no schema change required, only the rendering layer changes.
- 2026-04-12: ADR-022 janyas dropdown: use a filter input + renderJanyaList() closure pattern rather than a static flex-wrap — the closure captures the sorted janyas array and re-renders the list on every oninput event; toggling the panel resets the filter and re-focuses the input for immediate typing.

- 2026-04-12: ADR-023 raga wheel (third view): SVG z-order is DOM order — the only reliable way to keep all text above all circles is a module-level _labelLayer <g> that is re-appended as the last child of the viewport after every expansion step via _bringLabelsToFront(vp); never put labels inside their node <g>.
- 2026-04-12: ADR-023 label cleanup on collapse: use two CSS classes — sat-label (all satellite labels) and sat-label-musc (musician tier only) — so the janya click handler can clear comp+musc labels while the comp click handler clears only musc labels, without disturbing the layers above.
- 2026-04-12: ADR-023 mela compositions: _expandComps accepts any raga object (not just janyas), so calling it directly with the mela raga after _expandMela draws janyas gives mela ragas their own composition layer without any code duplication.
- 2026-04-12: Phase 1 render-refactor: extract a monolithic render.py into a carnatic/render/ package using a one-shot extraction script (_phase1_extract.py) that slices exact line ranges via splitlines(keepends=True) — safer than hand-editing a 3,634-line file; the script is committed as an audit trail and can be deleted in Phase 2.
- 2026-04-12: render_html() uses ERA_COLORS, ERA_LABELS, INSTRUMENT_SHAPES from the same module in the original file — when moving it to html_generator.py, add an explicit import from .graph_builder; the NameError only surfaces at runtime, not at import time, because the constants are referenced inside the function body not at module level.
- 2026-04-12: The \s SyntaxWarning in html_generator.py is a pre-existing issue in the embedded JS regex string inside the triple-quoted f-string — it is a warning not an error; Phase 2 (template extraction) will resolve it by moving the JS into a raw string or a separate file.

- 2026-04-13: ADR-025 raga wheel re-entry guard: when a wheel-internal click dispatches triggerBaniSearch → applyBaniFilter → syncRagaWheelToFilter → drawRagaWheel(), the circular chain collapses the expanded state. Guard with window._wheelSyncInProgress set before synthetic click dispatch and cleared in the final setTimeout callback; syncRagaWheelToFilter returns immediately if the flag is set.
- 2026-04-13: ADR-025 pan/zoom state must be module-level: any state that must survive a full SVG rebuild (innerHTML = '') cannot live in a closure inside drawRagaWheel. Lift _vx/_vy/_vscale/_dragging/_dragMoved to IIFE module scope; _applyTransform() must look up #wheel-viewport by ID (not close over a local vp reference) and be called immediately after vp is appended to restore the saved transform.
- 2026-04-13: ADR-025 drag-end fires click on background rect: a pan gesture (mousedown + mousemove + mouseup) ends with a click event on whatever element is under the pointer — in this case the transparent background rect, which calls _collapseAll. Guard with a _dragMoved flag (set when pointer moves >3px during drag) that suppresses the collapse handler and resets on the next mousedown.
- 2026-04-13: ADR-025 _triggerMelaExpand three-level dispatch: to highlight a specific comp node via syncRagaWheelToFilter, a third setTimeout is needed after the janya click settles. For mela-direct comps (no janya intermediary, targetRagaId=null), add an else-if branch that dispatches the comp click directly after the mela expansion settles — the janya branch is skipped entirely.

- 2026-04-13: Raga wheel music coverage bug: compsByRaga was built only from compositions.json compositions[]; ragas with no canonical compositions (e.g. hamir_kalyani) showed no satellite layer. Fix: three-source build — (1) compositions.json, (2) ragaToPerf structured recording performances, (3) elements[].data.tracks[] youtube entries. The tracks field (not youtube) is what graph_builder.py injects into Cytoscape elements. Synthetic items carry _isPerf:true so tooltip and _expandMusicians handle them via ragaToNodes fallback. _ytShortTitle() extracts the piece name before the first " · " or " - " separator to keep wheel node labels compact. Also fixed dead rtpByRaga loop which iterated rec.tracks (old flat schema) instead of rec.sessions[].performances (current nested schema).

- 2026-04-13: Raga wheel comp click path-lighting bug: the root cause was triggerBaniSearch inside the comp click handler calling syncRagaWheelToFilter → drawRagaWheel() (full SVG redraw), wiping all dimming state before it was visible; fix is window._wheelSyncInProgress = true around the triggerBaniSearch call so syncRagaWheelToFilter short-circuits.
- 2026-04-13: _expandMusicians had a parameter name collision: the cy parameter (center-Y number) shadowed the outer const cy (Cytoscape instance), causing cy.getElementById to throw TypeError; renamed to cyCY to restore lexical access to the Cytoscape global.
- 2026-04-13: Raga wheel musician ring is unwanted — the wheel is a navigation aid only; removed the _expandMusicians call from the comp click handler entirely; musician detail is surfaced via the bani sync to the graph view.
- 2026-04-13: isMelaDirect flag pattern: when _expandComps is called for a mela's own items (no janya intermediary), pass isMelaDirect=true so the comp click handler can hide the janya-group <g> and sat-label-janya labels; the janya-path call passes nothing (falsy); added sat-label-janya CSS class to janya labels to distinguish them from comp labels which share sat-label.
- 2026-04-13: _main.py now supports both direct invocation (python3 carnatic/render/_main.py) and the bani-render CLI entry point by injecting the project root into sys.path at startup and using absolute imports; __init__.py exposes a thin shim so pyproject.toml entry point carnatic.render:main resolves without circular imports; .clinerules updated to enforce source .venv/bin/activate before any bani-* command and bani-render as the canonical render invocation.

- 2026-04-13: `const` globals injected into a `<script>` block are NOT properties of `window` in modern browsers; guard with `typeof tanpuraData === 'undefined'` not `!window.tanpuraData` — the latter silently returns true even when the const is defined.
- 2026-04-13: Named-player registry pattern (ADR-029): a secondary `namedPlayerRegistry` keyed by a string `playerId` (e.g. `'sruti'`) is the correct way to manage singleton UI players that must coexist with the vid-keyed concert player registry; `openPlayer(vid, title, playerId)` + `closePlayer(playerId)` are the public API; the sruti player spawns at a fixed top-right position rather than the default stacked offset.

### 🏛️ Graph Architect

- 2026-04-12: ADR-023 proposes the raga wheel as a third view (SVG, not Cytoscape) — the circle is fixed geometry derived from the melakarta reference image; outer layers (janyas, compositions, musicians) emanate on demand via click; the three-way view selector replaces the binary Graph/Timeline toggle; no schema change required — all data is already present after ADR-021 migration; musician nodes bridge both views via triggerBaniSearch.

- 2026-04-11: When the same composition appears in both a structured recording file and a musicians.json youtube entry, the disambiguation is a `version` field (free text, e.g. "Jamshedpur 1961" or "standalone clip") — not a new object type; `composition_id` is the stable identity, `version` is the context label that survives the unified migration.
- 2026-04-12: .roomodes customInstructions values are single-line JSON strings; all .roomodes mutations must go through a dedicated transform script — never apply_diff directly on .roomodes.
- 2026-04-12: The PerformanceRef shape already carries recording_id, session_index, performers[], short_title, and date — the UI was discarding them by flattening; concert bracketing is always a rendering fix, never a schema change.
- 2026-04-12: Every new UI grouping (concert brackets, session sub-brackets) implies new CLI commands — concerts-for, co-performers-of, concerts-with must mirror what the browser shows so scholars and agents can query without opening the graph.


- 2026-04-13: ADR-027 proposes a reflective metadata popover (double-click any node/edge to inspect its full JSON data object in-browser); overhead is rendering-layer only — ~15 lines HTML, ~40 lines CSS, ~30 lines JS — because all data is already injected as JS globals by the render pipeline; the only breaking change is reassigning dbltap from Wikipedia-open to the inspector (Wikipedia remains accessible via the ↗ sidebar link).
- 2026-04-14: ADR-030 proposes view-selector restructure: (1) two primary views only — Guru-Shishya (parampara) and Mela-Janya (raga system) — replacing the three-way Graph/Timeline/Ragas selector; (2) Timeline demoted to a toggle within the Guru-Shishya view, changing currentView to a binary 'graph'|'raga' and using currentLayout for the graph/timeline sub-mode; (3) Fit/Reset/Relayout moved from the header into a compact #viewport-toolbar overlay at top-right of #canvas-wrap, with .vp-btn styling at 0.68rem/opacity:0.75; (4) Labels button and toggleLabels()/labelsOverride removed entirely — the zoom-tiered applyZoomLabels() is the correct and only label behaviour; (5) Mela-Janya view gains Fit/Reset parity via wheelFit()/wheelReset() stubs; pattern resolution: Levels of Scale + Strong Centres + Boundaries.
- 2026-04-18: ADR-032 Phase 0+1 implementation revealed five navigation failures invisible in DevTools but obvious on a real 390px device: (1) bottom sheet 72px peek is below the thumb rest zone and invisible; (2) left drawer has no visible close affordance; (3) media player competes with all panels without coordination; (4) filter chips scroll but have no visual overflow indicator; (5) view selector labels consume too much header width. ADR-036 (navigation choreography) and ADR-037 (media player docking) address these as a coordinated system.
- 2026-04-18: ADR-038/039/040 address six remaining mobile failures: redundant hamburger (same action as Trail tab → remove), tap-through on tab bar to canvas nodes beneath, musician bottom-sheet being inaccessible (convert to right drawer mirroring left Trail drawer), spatial mismatch (Trail button right but panel left → swap tab positions), filter chips clipped by nowrap overflow (→ wrap with full-width separator). Key pattern: dual-drawer symmetry (left=Trail, right=Musician) replaces the bottom-sheet-for-musician paradigm.
- 2026-04-18: ADR-041/042/043 form a cohesive interaction trilogy: (1) tab bar stays above scrim and acts as toggle — same tap opens and closes, removing ✕ buttons, renaming "Trail" → "Bani Flow"; (2) canvas clicks auto-open the affinity drawer (Guru-Shishya node → Musician, Mela-Janya raga/comp → Bani Flow) — the overlay-on-expansion dilemma for raga wheel is acknowledged as accepted trade-off with toggle-dismiss escape; (3) play button reveals mini-player inline between drawer and tab bar, compressing drawer content by 56px rather than displacing it.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-073/074 close the visual-coupling loop named in ADR-025: panel chips (ADR-063) already encode entity identity via colour (teal=raga, amber=comp, era-tinted=musician) but the centre views render the same entities in a uniform dark `THEME.labelOutline` pill — ADR-073 retints raga-wheel satellite labels (janya, comp) using the existing chip tokens via SVG attributes (mela rim labels exempt to preserve cakra colour), ADR-074 retints guru-shishya graph node labels by extending `data(color)` into new `data(label_outline)`/`data(label_bg)` fields and lowering `text-background-opacity` from 0.65 to ~0.18 so the era tint matches the panel chip's `color-mix(... 12%, transparent)` look at Cytoscape fidelity; key insight: visual coupling needs no schema change — the era and chip-token vocabularies already exist, the centre views just have to consume them.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-077..082 introduce the lecdem as a first-class object via a six-ADR sequence (schema → render indexes → chip identity → musician panel sections → bani-flow strip + discoverability invariant → CLI/forms entry); key architectural moves are (1) reuse the `youtube[]` container with a `kind` discriminator and a `subjects` object instead of inventing a new top-level file, mirroring the ADR-070 pattern of optional facets on tracks, (2) skip lecdems in the listenable-set indexer so ADR-055 no-dead-ends semantics stay stable while four new `lecdems_by`/`lecdems_about_*` indexes serve discovery-only surfaces, (3) codify scratch.md item 9's "discovery-not-lookup" requirement as three concrete negative invariants — no global search inclusion, no topbar filter, no deep-link URL — that can be enforced with grep tests at the search-index builder, the filter-chip array, and the URL parser, (4) make the empty-`subjects` "lecdem about everything and nothing" case (item 6) a first-class schema state with a single render surface (host's "Lecdems by" section only), and (5) push entry hygiene to the boundary by requiring combobox-only subject pickers in the form and resolvable `--about-*` ids in the CLI, with a deliberately friction-ful "open the entity-creation form in a new window" escape hatch for missing entities — matching the spirit of ADR-077 invariant D's no-unmatched-name policy on subjects.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-083/084/085 close the lecdem loop and elevate the bundle to a constitutional contract: ADR-083 ratifies `bani_add_bundle.json` (envelope + six whitelisted item buckets + fixed processing order + `schema_version` gate) as the single browser→disk write channel, requiring `addToBundle` and `bani_add` to hard-fail on unknown keys instead of silently dropping, and unifying the on-disk `youtube[]` element shape with the bundle's `YoutubeEntryItem` so lecdems flow without translation; ADR-084 specifies the three-line plumbing (`writer.add_youtube` grows `kind`/`subjects`/`ragas_path` kwargs as the sole validation site, `bani_add._process_musicians` forwards them blindly, `write_cli.py` builds `subjects` from repeatable `--about-*` flags) — the writer is the only layer that knows lecdem semantics; ADR-085 names the loop (graph.html → bundle → bani-add → writer → entity files → render → graph.html) as a self-replicating, self-editing system and binds future ADRs to it: every new write surface MUST produce a bundle, never write directly; every new readable entity type MUST come with an entry surface or an explicit follow-up ADR; deletions/renames remain explicitly out-of-loop; the loop's safety is the joint product of bundle whitelist + writer single-validation-site + render idempotence.
- 2026-04-23: ADR-086 makes the empty panel itself the README: when the Bani Flow / Musician panels have no subject loaded, render a `panel-tutorial` block (headline + mechanics bullets + 2–6 clickable seed examples) drawn from a new `data/help/empty_panels.json` whose `id` / `recording_ref` / `lecdem_ref` fields are validated by `cli.py validate` so tutorial bit-rot fails CI; the tutorial is the panel's null state (not a banner), dissolves atomically when a subject is loaded, returns when the subject is cleared, and adapts mechanics copy to current view (`graph` vs `raga`); the musician panel's last bullet must surface `+ Performer` / `+ Lecdem` to make the ADR-085 self-replicating loop visible from the very first paint; seed examples reference verified ids (`tyagaraja` compositions, `ramnad_krishnan` Poonamalee 1965 tracks, `tm_krishna` lecdems, `thodi`, `parulanna_matta`) — `recording_ref` and `lecdem_ref` are deliberate soft pointers `(musician_id, concert_hint, raga_id)` so renaming a recording does not silently break the seed; `help.md` is not deprecated — narrative help and contextual panel help serve different jobs.
### 🎵 Carnatic Coder

- 2026-04-15: ADR-031 (entry_forms.js): The Cytoscape `elements` array does NOT use `{group: 'nodes', data: {...}}` format — elements are flat `{data: {...}}` objects; distinguish nodes from edges by `!e.data.source` (edges have `data.source`/`data.target`). The `e.group === 'nodes'` filter silently returns an empty array.

- 2026-04-15: ADR-031 (entry_forms.js): The render pipeline converts musician `youtube[].url` → `vid` (11-char YouTube ID) when building Cytoscape elements (`e.data.tracks`). The "Add YouTube to Existing Musician" form must normalise `{vid}` back to `{url: "https://youtu.be/{vid}"}` before writing the output JSON, or the downloaded file will have inconsistent field names.

- 2026-04-15: ADR-031 (entry_forms.js): `wireCompRagaAutofill(compSel, ragaSel, composerSel, formWin)` is the correct pattern for composition→raga/composer auto-fill. Pass `null` for `composerSel` in YouTube blocks (no composer field there).

- 2026-04-15: ADR-031 (entry_forms.js): `write_to_file` truncates at the tool content limit — always use `apply_diff` to append the remainder. Large JS files (>600 lines) should be written in two passes.

- 2026-04-15: ADR-031 (graphData): `graphData.nodes` must carry full musician fields (sources, born, died, era, instrument, bani) — the "Add YouTube to Existing Musician" form needs them to reconstruct the complete musician JSON.

- 2026-04-18: ADR-037 (mobile media player docking): The mobile singleton player appends to `document.body` (not `#main`) because it uses `position: fixed` docking. Desktop players append to `#main` with `position: absolute` and drag/resize — these two paths are fully separate via the `_isMobilePlayer()` gate in `openOrFocusPlayer()`. The `_currentPanelState` getter on `window` bridges the mobile.js IIFE scope into media_player.js for panel save/restore.

- 2026-04-18: ADR-042 graph-to-drawer coupling: selectNode() in graph_view.js already called setPanelState('MUSICIAN') — no change needed there. The raga wheel has two code paths: mela/janya clicks use applyBaniFilter directly (not triggerBaniSearch) to avoid wheel re-entry, so setPanelState('TRAIL') must be added at both call sites in raga_wheel.js plus inside triggerBaniSearch in bani_flow.js for composition clicks.
- 2026-04-19: ADR-044 click-again affordance nudge: a single shared #click-nudge div (pointer-events:none, fixed bottom-center, z-index 9999) is the correct pattern for cross-view transient hints — it sits outside both the SVG raga wheel and the Cytoscape canvas so no coordinate mapping is needed; showClickNudge/hideClickNudge live on window via an IIFE in base.html so both raga_wheel.js and graph_view.js can call them without import coupling.

- 2026-04-18: ADR-035 pointer capture + preventDefault() on pointerdown suppresses ALL native click and dblclick events on the raga wheel SVG. Synthetic clicks (from _triggerMelaExpand via dispatchEvent) still work, masking the bug when navigating from panels. Fix: in _onPointerEnd, use document.elementFromPoint to resolve the real target under the pointer and re-dispatch a synthetic click when _dragMoved is false.
- 2026-04-21: ADRs 052–057 split a UX coupling pass into six independent concerns — click parity, timestamp removal + concert play-button affordance, era-coloured musician chips, no-dead-end musician filtering and graph dimming, equal chip prominence with secondary fallback, and a composer panel that lists compositions instead of recordings; the unifying force is "panels and graph are one data set, two representations" — chip colour must equal node colour, and every clickable thing must lead somewhere listenable.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-070/071 (youtube performers): a new optional field on a legacy schema only earns its keep when its absence and presence behave identically to the renderer — the trick is a single helper (`_track_performer_ids(host, yt)`) that returns `[host]` when `performers[]` is missing and the explicit list otherwise, then both indexers (`build_composition_lookups`, `build_listenable_set`) walk it instead of hard-coding the host; the two invariants (host-implicit when omitted, host-included when present) live in the validator, not in the writer's normaliser, so out-of-band edits also get caught.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-071 (entry_forms): nested form sections (Accompanists inside a YouTube block) break positional `querySelectorAll('input')` indexing — switch to `:scope > .ef-row input` so the parent's collector ignores descendants of the new container; mirror the role vocabulary from `roles.py` to a `roles.js` window global injected before `entry_forms.js` so the dropdown source-of-truth is one Python tuple.
- 2026-04-22: cli.py imports must be absolute (`from carnatic.render.roles import VALID_ROLES`), not relative — it runs as a script (sibling-imports `carnatic.graph_api`), so `from .render.roles` raises `ImportError: attempted relative import with no known parent package`.

- 2026-04-22: Accompanist youtube entries (Carnatic convention: vocalist = primary artist) should live on the vocalist's node, not the accompanist's; when clearing a musician's youtube array always verify all entries are already present on the primary artist's node by video ID before deletion — 67 of 69 Akkarai Subbulakshmi entries were already duplicated on TM Krishna; the 2 apparently unique ones were already duplicated under a different URL format, caught by write_cli's video_id dedup guard.
- 2026-04-23: When a concert tracklist composer is listed only by ankita/honorific form (e.g. "Dharmapuri Subbarayar" → dharmapuri_subbaraya_iyer, "Ramanathapuram Srinivasa Iyangar" → ramnad_sreenivasa_iyengar, "Parulanamata" → parulanna_matta), always resolve to the canonical DB entry before creating a new node — run composition-exists and composer name variants; "Subbarayar" is the Tamil honorific of "Subbaraya Iyer" and "Ramanathapuram" is the toponym for "Ramnad"; a direct duplicate would have been created for parulanna_matta without the user's catch.
- 2026-04-23: Raga aliases added this session: sriranjini += "Sriranjani", arabhi += "Aarabhi", pantuvarali += "Panthuvarali". Composition aliases added: ninnada title changed to "Ninnada Nela" (alias "Ninnada"), samayamide_rara += alias "Samayamithe", laavanya_rama_kannul_ara += alias "Lavanya Rama", parulanna_matta += alias "Parulanamata". Always add these alternate spellings when encountered in concert listings — they are the source of future false "NOT FOUND" lookups.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-070 cross-link symmetry: data layer alone is not enough — every render path must surface the new association the same way; `buildTreeRaga` always calls `buildTreeLeaf`, but `buildTreeComp` short-circuits single-version groups to render only a header (no leaf), so co-performers vanished in the comp view; fix is to mirror the multi-version `.tree-leaf-coperformers` block under the single-version header. Likewise the right-panel `rec-filter` searched only `.tree-comp-node` text, so a raga-name query (the very label the user clicks on the wheel) hid every group whose leaves only show comp titles — include `.tree-group-header` text so the chip itself is searchable.
- 2026-04-22: Bani Flow tree groups (raga + comp views) now open by default — discoverability beats chrome economy; the chevron toggle remains so users can collapse, but a first-time searcher sees the full tree without having to spot a drop-down affordance. One-line change in `buildTreeRaga`/`buildTreeComp`: drop the `isFirst`-only gating and always add `tree-group-open`.
- 2026-04-22: Lecdems must be excluded from `graph_builder.py` `tracks[]` (filter `t.get("kind") == "lecdem"`) so they never appear in the misc/raga tree; the three lecdem render surfaces (musician "by", musician "about", bani-flow strip) must all use the `trail-row2 / trail-chips / trail-acts` play-button pattern, not `buildLecdemChip`, so the label wraps to 2 lines and the ▶ / ↗ buttons remain right-aligned — CSS overrides go on `.lecdem-row` following the same approach as `.tree-misc-leaf`.
- 2026-04-22: ADR-083 (bundle as canonical write channel): the two safety rails are (1) a `MAX_VERSION` constant + `> MAX_VERSION` check in `bani_add.py` (not `!= 1`, so future schema versions get a clear upgrade message), and (2) iterating `items.keys()` against a `KNOWN_ITEM_TYPES` frozenset before touching any processor — both checks exit before any items are processed, so a rogue key can never silently pass; `addToBundle` in `entry_forms.js` uses `type in baniBundle` (not `!baniBundle[type]`) so a key whose array is empty still passes rather than throwing a false positive.
- 2026-04-23: ADR-086 (empty-panel tutorials): the loader / global / validator triplet must be absence-tolerant from day one — `load_help_empty_panels` returns `None`, `helpEmptyPanels` ships as the literal `null`, and the JS shows/hides become silent no-ops, so the Coder PR can land before the Librarian writes `data/help/empty_panels.json`; render-time injection of soft pointers (`recording_ref`, `lecdem_ref`) is a trap (recording IDs drift) so resolution is deferred to JS click time using `musicianToPerformances` (substring match on `recording_id` or `title` + exact `raga_id`); the validator mirrors that resolution exactly so a stale hint fails CI loudly instead of silently navigating nowhere; the show/hide hooks live at the same two sites as every other "panel cleared" / "panel populated" handler — `clearBaniFilter` / `buildListeningTrail` for the left panel and the `cy.on('tap', evt => ...)` background handler / `selectNode` for the right — keeping the tutorial's lifetime exactly equal to the panel's null-state lifetime with no extra state machine.

### 🪃 Orchestrator

- 2026-04-23: Lecdem lecturer attribution must be a first-class `.musician-chip` (era-tinted, clickable, navigates via `selectNode` + `setPanelState('MUSICIAN')`) — not a `.lecdem-by` plain-text span; the `_buildLecturerChip(id, label)` helper lives in media_player.js (loaded before bani_flow.js per html_generator.py script ordering) so both the musician-panel "about" subsection and the Bani Flow strip can call it. Lecturer chip + subject chips share one `.lecdem-subjects` wrap container so they flow as a single tag cloud rather than stacking lecturer on its own line.
